---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="What RSM Claims">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">What RSM Claims (And Doesn't)</h1>
      <p class="themed-text-muted">A boundary-setting document</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Core Claim -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Core Claim</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <p class="themed-text-secondary mb-3">
          <strong>RSM claims one thing:</strong> <em>if</em> reality is infinitely vast and infinitely divisible, then a single structural pattern follows necessarily — stable structures persist by circulating around a crossing their frame never meets, and are generated at a crossing that is met but can never become a frame of its own. The claim is conditional; the derivation is what's checkable; the renderings into physics and biology are correspondences that carry no evidential weight of their own. <span class="font-mono text-sm">[candidate]</span>
        </p>
        <p class="themed-text-secondary">
          The Dao De Jing is deliberately not on that list. The framework grew out of the text, so their agreement is not evidence of anything. The DDJ is the subject of translation here.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="themed-text-secondary">
        That's it. That's the claim. Everything below is a way of being careful about it — what's an empirical prediction you could test, what's an interesting analogy, and what the framework deliberately says nothing about.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- What RSM Predicts -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What RSM Predicts (Empirically Testable)</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">This is the framework's only evidential section. Every other correspondence on this site carries zero evidential weight. Each prediction requires preregistration before any check counts.</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="themed-border border-b">
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">Prediction</th>
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">Status</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="themed-text-secondary">
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Cross-frame unit relations, if closed, take power-law form between nesting levels — operationalized through measured RG critical exponents and/or the holographic area law.</td>
              <td class="align-top"><span class="font-mono text-sm">[falsifiable — target]</span><br /><span class="text-sm themed-text-muted">The framework must derive the exponent-form before the check. Currently a target.</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Structural recession gives a signature distinguishable from ΛCDM.</td>
              <td class="align-top"><span class="font-mono text-sm">[falsifiable — unbuilt]</span><br /><span class="text-sm themed-text-muted">The distinguishing observational signature is the explicit open task. Unbuilt.</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Unitarity holds. Objective-collapse theories violate it by design, are empirically live, and are increasingly constrained; their confirmation would strike the floor's dynamical face directly.</td>
              <td class="align-top"><span class="font-mono text-sm">[falsifiable]</span><br /><span class="text-sm themed-text-muted">A genuine kill-condition.</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 text-sm">Earlier versions carried further predictions. They are not restated here pending re-verification against source — the current chain declines to reproduce them from memory, and so does this page.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- What RSM Suggests -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What RSM Suggests (Structural Analogies)</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">These are pattern recognitions. Interesting, possibly insightful, but not derivations or proofs.</p>
      <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-2">-</span>
          DDJ Chapter 1 reads as a coordinate system
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-2">-</span>
          DDJ Chapter 11 encodes O<sub>1</sub> geometry
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-2">-</span>
          Euler's identity is "Contrast, Rotation, Closure" in five symbols
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-2">-</span>
          Zero is better understood as "generative" than "empty"
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-2">-</span>
          Hurricane eyes, tree pith, and atomic nuclei share O<sub>1</sub> structure
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Analogies invite investigation. They don't constitute evidence.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- What RSM Does NOT Claim -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What RSM Does NOT Claim</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">These are explicitly outside the framework's scope. Not "not yet addressed" - deliberately excluded.</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <table class="w-full text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="themed-border border-b">
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">Topic</th>
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">RSM Position</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="themed-text-secondary">
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Consciousness</td>
              <td>No claim. Pattern recognition doesn't explain experience.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Physics</td>
              <td>Rendering only — every entry is a correspondence ("maps to," never "is") with zero evidential weight, except the preregistered predictions above. RSM does not derive ℏ, the ½, or Fourier conjugacy.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Metaphysics</td>
              <td>No claim. RSM describes structure, not whether things "really exist."</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Cosmology</td>
              <td>No claim. Whether the universe "requires" this structure is unknown.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Ethics</td>
              <td>No claim. Description, not prescription. How to live is your business.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Theology</td>
              <td>No claim. "Generative center" is not God, Tao, or Brahman.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Ancient author intent</td>
              <td>No claim. Parallel patterns don't mean Laozi "knew" this.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Reference -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Quick Reference</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="themed-text-secondary mb-3"><strong>"Does RSM claim X?"</strong></p>
        <ol class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
          <li>Is X the core pattern itself (centers, gradients, boundaries, recursion)? <strong>Claimed.</strong></li>
          <li>Is X an empirical mapping (plant biology, Kleiber, etc.)? <strong>Predicted, testable.</strong></li>
          <li>Is X a structural analogy (DDJ readings, Euler interpretation)? <strong>Suggested, not proven.</strong></li>
          <li>Is X about consciousness, physics fundamentals, metaphysics, or ethics? <strong>Not claimed.</strong></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The One-Liner -->
    <section class="mb-12 text-center themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
      <p class="themed-text-secondary text-lg">
        <strong>The one-liner:</strong> RSM describes one pattern of persistence and tries to be honest about which of its claims are math, which are empirical tests, and which are interesting analogies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="text-center themed-text-muted text-sm themed-border border-t pt-8">
      <p class="italic mb-2">Pattern, not proof. Description, not prescription.</p>
      <p class="mb-4"><a href="/confidence" style="color: var(--color-accent);">See the Confidence Map</a> | <a href="/faq" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Read the FAQ</a></p>
      <p>Will Goldstein &amp; Claude — December 2025</p>
    </footer>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
